commit.message: Remove unused rubocops

Do not use shorthand hash syntax because jruby

JRuby targets 2.6, and doesn't support this syntax. JRuby 9.3 is still supported: https://github.com/jruby/jruby/wiki/Roadmap

When JRuby 9.3 isn't supported any more, we can drop it.
Do not test on 3.0
Update changelog

Update rubocop target ruby to 3.1

We can't make a new release with this just yet, because we still support Ruby 3.0 for another 30 days.

Do not early exit when a required job fails

We still want to run all tests fully, but the job as a whole should be considered failed.

Allow running test-suite on demand on main

There was a recent test failure on a PR, which I believe is of no fault of the PR itself.

I'd like to be able to run the test suite manually too.

commit.message:
Fix references to `master` that should be `main`

Not sure what inch is, but at least the branch isn't wrong?
Add status badge for main CI build
There's no need to upload coverage artifacts.

Bundler-cache does not work with rubocop

… for whatever reason. I tried bumping the cache, I tried upgrading rubocop, and nothing else works.

We don't need no ruby directive in Gemfile

Docs: https://bundler.io/guides/gemfile_ruby.html

This is not needed for us. The gemfile is only used for development.

This directive is causing issues when running on ruby 3.3.0.dev, because `RUBY_VERSION` reports as `3.3.0` but bundler picks it up as `3.3.0.dev` and then rejects the Gemfile.

Add collection step for jobs

This allows us to configure which jobs must pass in order to be able to merge a PR.

It's still useful to be able to run jobs that doesn't have to succeed for a PR to merge.

Add github actions for running test suite on PRs

No particular reason.
